<font color="#FF0000">SOME THOUGHTS FOR ALEX</font><br>
<tt>Sat Mar 15  7:09:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Alex,<br><br>
The creepy part is that Chris' thoughts *do* sound like those of others, but he was just born when we were in full swing in the Vietnam vortex.<br><br>
Are may of us locked in our own &quot;time warp&quot;? I, personally, did not know what to expect when I started posting on this site many months ago, having kept it all inside myself for all these years. It has taken me a lot of work over the past few years just to arrive at this point. <br><br>
What I see here right now from Chris is not the shabby, discriminatory, borderline treasonous, denegrating, and just plain awful, treatment and characterization of the Vietnam Veteran, the proverbial scapegoat of the malfesance of society and government. What I see here is the separation of the Vietnam Veteran from the *system* which put all of us in the mess in the first place. That is Chris' point.<br><br>
It find it really cool to be treated like a human being for a change, and respected for my label as a Vietnam Veteran. I still wrench inside at my flashback to Oakland, CA, and my first few hours of &quot;freedom&quot; from the Vietnam War. As I have said elsewhere, I really learned there, in Oakland, what it must have felt like (in 1950's words) for &quot;colored people&quot; to &quot;sit in the back of the bus&quot;.<br><br>
I feel that I, and perhaps many of us, need to break into the present. Although I may not agree with some of Chris' views, and I may feel there are additional things he should consider, we must face the fact that he represents the present, or at least a part of the present who is not shy about expressing their views.<br><br>
Alex, your thoughts on changing the system are really parallel to those of Chris. Lets not discourage people like Chris without first giving them due consideration of their ideas. If someone is an idiot, I know we are not shy with the tar and feathers. If someone isn't, then I feel we have to look a little closer.<br><br>
Arthur   <br><br>

